                "sections": [
                    {
                        "title": "Summary & Transition",
                        "content": "<p>Excellent work. You've just organized the Module 4 landscape the way an expert would. You've built a mental model of how platforms relate to categories and to each other.</p><p>Notice that the field isn't fixed boxes; it's a spectrum. You can now place any new platform you encounter by asking: What's its core purpose? Who does it serve? What evidence backs it?</p><p><strong>In Module 4, you learned what exists and how to navigate it.</strong></p><p><strong>In Module 5, you'll learn who builds all of this, how the field sustains itself, and where you might fit within it.</strong></p><p>The applications you just mapped are made possible by a broader ecosystemâ€”researchers, investors, facilitators, regulators, and communities all working in relationship. Let's explore the system that makes the landscape possible.</p>",
                        "triggerLabel": "Complete Module 4"
                    }
                ]
            }
